modules.description: This module implements a rate limiter for controlling data transmission speeds in asynchronous file transfers. It works with byte rate limits specified in bytes per second and tracks the state of data sent over time. Concrete use cases include throttling network uploads or limiting disk I/O during file copying operations.

This module enables efficient file transmission over file descriptors using the `sendfile(2)` system call, with support for rate-limited sending and optional flow control. It provides core operations for sending files with byte-level precision and integrates a rate limiter that enforces byte-per-second constraints, making it suitable for throttling network uploads or managing disk I/O. The main data types include file descriptors, byte counters, and limiter configurations, with key operations for initiating sends and adjusting transmission rates. Example usage includes serving static files over sockets without user-space buffering while capping bandwidth consumption.
